      <h1 class='title'>Official Report of the Grand Committee on the Companies Act 1985 (Operating and Financial Review and Directors' Report etc.) Regulations 2005</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 21 February 2005 vol 669 cc181-226GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_181gc' title='Col. 181GC &mdash; HL Deb 21 February 2005 vol 669 c181GC' name='column_181gc' href='#column_181gc' rel='bookmark'>181GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03174'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_1' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="bold">Monetary and Fiscal Policy (EAC Report)</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03175'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_2' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="bold">Child Trust Funds (Amendment) Regulations 2005</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03176'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_3' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="bold"><a href="/acts/government-resources-and-accounts-act-2000">Government Resources and Accounts Act 2000</a> (Audit of Public Bodies) Order 2005</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03177'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_4' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="italic">Monday, 21 February 2005.</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03178'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_5' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="bold">The Committee met at half past three of the clock.</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0669P0-03179'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_6' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [The Deputy Chairman of Committees (Lord Ampthill) in the Chair.]
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-03180'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-geoffrey-russell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050221_GCR_7' title='Link to this speech by Mr Geoffrey Russell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-geoffrey-russell" title="Mr Geoffrey Russell">The Deputy Chairman of Committees (Lord Ampthill)</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Before the Minister moves the first order to be considered, it may be helpful for me to say a word about the procedure for today's Grand Committee. Our proceedings are essentially the same as those in the House. Noble Lords will speak standing. All noble Lords are free to attend and participate and the proceedings will be reported in <span class="italic">Hansard.</span></p><p>
            As there is more than one item of business today, each item will be called on by the Clerk. So far as concerns the regulations and order which are to be debated today, I should perhaps make it clear to noble Lords that this Committee is charged only to consider these items, not to approve or not approve them. The Motions to approve will in due course be moved in the Chamber in the usual way.</p><p>
            If there is a Division in the Chamber while we are sitting, this Committee will adjourn as soon as the Division bells are rung and resume after 10 minutes.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
